H0.text: Name the Archbishop of Canterbury who was burnt at the stake in 1556. John Fisher

H1.text: Name the Archbishop of Canterbury who was burnt at the stake in 1556. Thomas Becket

H2.text: Name the Archbishop of Canterbury who was burnt at the stake in 1556. Matthew Parker

H3.text: Name the Archbishop of Canterbury who was burnt at the stake in 1556. Cranmer

A4.text: Thomas Cranmer was burned at the stake on 21 March 1556.

A5.text: Thomas Cranmer was Archbishop of Canterbury during the reigns of Henry VIII, Edward VI, and Mary I.
